November district council elections,

240
00:12:20,800 --> 00:12:22,589
the localists and the Democrats

241
00:12:22,589 --> 00:12:25,170
will have a strong political comeback.

242
00:12:25,170 --> 00:12:29,370
However, whether the government of officials,

243
00:12:29,370 --> 00:12:33,180
including the electoral officials responsible
for elections,

244
00:12:33,180 --> 00:12:37,999
whether they allow some localists to run in
the elections

245
00:12:37,999 --> 00:12:39,519
remains to be seen

246
00:12:39,519 --> 00:12:43,119
and it will probably become a controversial
issue

247
00:12:43,119 --> 00:12:45,899
because some localists advocate the idea

248
00:12:45,899 --> 00:12:49,279
of quote self determination end of quote,

249
00:12:49,279 --> 00:12:52,420
which is legally and politically unacceptable

250
00:12:52,420 --> 00:12:55,660
to both Beijing and the Hong Kong authorities.

251
00:12:55,660 --> 00:12:57,129
So there's going to be an effort

252
00:12:57,129 --> 00:12:59,899
to make sure pro-Beijing forces win?

253
00:12:59,899 --> 00:13:05,569
There will be such a thrust to ensure that
candidates who are,

254
00:13:05,569 --> 00:13:10,529
you know, relatively pro-Beijing who support
the basic law

255
00:13:10,529 --> 00:13:13,189
and also the SAR government

256
00:13:13,189 --> 00:13:15,589
will be allowed to run in the election.

257
00:13:15,589 --> 00:13:19,639
However, the localists who are now anti government,

258
00:13:19,639 --> 00:13:21,060
anti China,

259
00:13:21,060 --> 00:13:25,119
they may face the possibility of being

260
00:13:25,119 --> 00:13:27,709
disallowed to run in the election.

